sdgs.relevance:
Aam Digital is used by social sector organizations that directly work with beneficiaries on the ground. As a customizable software platform it is contributing to the work of organizations working towards a number of SDGs:

Projects use Aam Digital to track & coordinate
- living conditions and interventions to improve livelihoods (SDG 1);
- beneficiaries' health status and health-related activities (SDG 3);
- student support programs, learning progress and attendance at educational activities (SDG 4);
- work focused on gender equity and girls' rights (SDG 5);
- activities of capacity building for SMEs and their outcomes (SDG 8);
- work with marginalized communities (SDG 10)
- activities to overcome conflict and stereotypes (SDG 16)
- ... and with its data management and reporting Aam Digital provides an easy way to evaluate and communicate work between partnerships across the globe with transparency and accountability (SDG 16)

